@Database Changes_To_V1.02.guide

@Node Main "Changes to HydraBBS between V1.01 and V1.02"

  Changes to HydraBBS between V1.01 and V1.02
  ===========================================

  Please read *ALL* of this file, or you won't know about some of the great
  new features of this release.

  Go on, it'll only take you a couple of minutes.

  This document is stored as HBBS:Docs/Misc/Upgrades/Changes_To_V1.02.Guide


  Details
  =======

  Sysop Information     - @{"More..." link SysopInformation}

  Developer Information - @{"More..." link HBBS:Developer/Docs/Upgrades/Dev_Changes_V1.02.guide/MAIN}

  Files Changed         - @{"More..." link FilesChanged}

@EndNode

@Node SysopInformation "Sysop Information"

  Sysop Information
  =================

  * Control

    After a couple of people tried to run HBBS without reading the quickstart
    guide (tut, bloody tut) I have changed the way Control starts and have
    added more error messages to it if something should fail early on.

    Added @{"NodeDescription_XX" link HBBS:Docs/Configuration/NodeList.guide/NodeDescription_XX} option to @{"HBBS:Nodes/NodeList" link HBBS:Docs/Configuration/NodeList.guide/Main}
    Control displays the first 10 chars instead of "Node xx" in it's window
    for each node that you specify a description for.

    Locks out the user data file until it's existance has been checked.

  * HBBSCommon.library

    Developers, please read @{" HBBS:Developer/Docs/Upgrades/Dev_Changes_V1.02.guide " link HBBS:Developer/Docs/Upgrades/Dev_Changes_V1.02.guide/MAIN}

    Changed SendMessage() to NOT call Forbit() and Permit() when sending a
    message from one task to another, this results in all door
    communications being faster and a better overall system speed on
    multinode or heavily multitasking machines.

    Fixed HBBS_RunDOSCMD, it wouldn't run any commands until struct BBSGlobal
    had been initialised. (i.e. this ever happens unless you manually
    screw about with the assigns or don't run the "Setup" script!!)

    HBBS_DoErrorMessage() was adding an extra space to the end of the command
    line, fixed. This caused no problems however...

    Optimized UpperCase(), smaller and faster now.

    Added better low memory checking and handling to quite a few routines.

    Two new functions added: HBBS_LockUserData() and HBBS_UnLockUserData()

    HBBS_AddCfgItemQuick(), Added low memory checking.

    HBBS_HandleNameOK(), Made smaller, faster and checks for more
    characters now.

    HBBS_AddUser(), fixed a potential loss of the last user in the user
    data file when overwriting an existing user failed. (Extremley unlikely!)

    Finished the HBBS_LoadUser() function, and changed the way it works.

    HBBS_ValidUserHandle(), recoded routine to use HBBS_LoadUser()

    HBBS_SaveUserData(), Now logs error messages if things don't go as
    planned.

    HBBS_ApplyAccountDefaults(), Added

    HBBS_AccessName(), Added

  * BulletinViewer

    When called with the name of a bulletin that exists, a pause
    prompt is displays.

    When in interactive mode the door will not display a pause prompt before
    returning you to the menu (the same as a pause prompt).  So now you can
    go through the bulletins much easier!

  * Node

    The node now shows you the name of the serial device name and unit number
    if it fails to open the device.

  * ErrorMessage (the program used to display error messages that is..)

    Wasn't displaying error messages with space's in the strings correctly

  * XPR

    It now updates the node window's CPS/BAUD with the current CPS rate.

  * Hydra

    It now displays both rx and tx CPS rates in the window.

    It now updates the node window's CPS/BAUD with the tx CPS rate.
    (i.e. the user's download CPS rate)

  * UserViewer

    Now displays CPS when a user is transferring a file

    GUI changed so that the colours are correct on an 8+ colour screen

  * AccountEditor

    When changing the user's handle, it now checks for invalid characters
    using HBBS_HandleNameOK()

    It also used HBBS_ApplyAccountDefaults().

    See @{"HBBS:Docs/Doors/AccountEdit.guide" link HBBS:Docs/Doors/AccountEdit.guide/ValidatingAUser} and
    @{"HBBS:Docs/Configuration/AccountDefaults.Guide" link HBBS:Docs/Configuration/AccountDefaults.Guide/MAIN} for details.

  * NewUser

    Added call to HBBS_ApplyAccountDefaults(), so when a new user joins
    they will have the account defaults applied for what ever level is
    given to a new user as specified in the newuser door's config file.

    See also:

    HBBS:Doors/System/NewUser/NewUser.CFG
    @{"HBBS:Docs/Configuration/AccountDefaults.Guide" link HBBS:Docs/Configuration/AccountDefaults.Guide/MAIN}

  * Example Configs

    Created some default "AccountDefaults" template files.  The installer
    will have copied them to:

    HBBS:Storage/Example_Configs/System/Data/AccountDefaults/

    *AND*

    HBBS:System/Data/AccountDefaults/

    Even when upgrading from V1.01.  (They're new configs!)

  * UserSettings

    Changed to use HBBS_HandleInUse(), so that it doesn't write to the user
    data file twice, possibly resulting in incorrect data in the user file
    if the system was rebooted between the two writes.  It now only writes
    to the file once, with the correct data!

    Also, it uses HBBS_HandleNameOK() now to check for invalid characters
    in the handle! (oops!)  But with the default configs the users can't
    change their handle anyway, so i doubt you have a problem.

    To be sure, check all user accounts for the following characters and
    change if needed: =;?*#

  * Spelling Mistakes

    Fixed spelling misake of "Preferred" (was "Prefered")

    Updated the following parts of the system:

      HBBS:Developer/Include/HBBS/structures.h
      HBBS:Doors/System/Node
      HBBS:Docs/Reference/Screens.guide
      HBBS:Doors/User/AccountEditor/AccountEditor.HBBS
      HBBS:Doors/User/Joinconference/JoinConference.HBBS
      HBBS:Doors/User/Joinconference/OldJoinConference.HBBS

@EndNode

